title: Subgraph of pango XBK/XBK.1/XBQ/CJ.1.3: (27 samples, 27 shown)
preamble: XBK and XBQ are siblings, and neither appear to be recombinants, as they are closely related to the non-recombinant node that originates CJ.1.3. It appears that our tree-building has reconstructed the upper internal node labelled CJ.1. This happens to support a hypothesis made at the time of defining XBK, that a missing common ancestor could exist (and make this non-recombinant). See https://github.com/cov-lineages/pango-designation/issues/1440#issuecomment-1355264973.See GitHub sc2ts-paper issue #349
